{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The DNA sequence of the entire colicin E2 operon has been determined [[cite:PUB00006230]]. The operon comprises the colicin activity gene (ceaB), the colicin immunity gene (ceiB) and the lysis gene (celB), which is essential for colicin release from producing cells [[cite:PUB00006230]]. A putative LexA binding site is located upstream from ceaB, and a rho-independent terminator structure is located downstream from celB [[cite:PUB00006230]]. Comparison of the amino acid sequences of colicin E2 and cloacin DF13 reveal extensive similarity. These colicins have different modes of action and recognise different cell surface receptors; the two major regions of heterology at the C terminus, and in the C-terminal end of the central region are thought to correspond to the catalytic and receptor-recognition domains, respectively [[cite:PUB00006230]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"prints" {"PR01297" "LYSISCOLICIN"}, "pfam" {"PF02402" "Lysis protein"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Colicin lysis protein", "short" "Lysis_col"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 2, "proteomes" 5, "taxa" 160, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 220, "sets" 0, "proteins" 220, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 167}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR003059", :literature {"PUB00006228" {"URL" nil, "issue" "19", "authors" ["van den Elzen PJ" "Gaastra W" "Spelt CE" "de Graaf FK" "Veltkamp E" "Nijkamp HJ."], "ISO_journal" "Nucleic Acids Res.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/nar/8.19.4349", "medline_journal" "Nucleic Acids Res", "title" "Molecular structure of the immunity gene and immunity protein of the bacteriocinogenic plasmid Clo DF13.", "year" 1980, "raw_pages" "4349-63", "volume" "8", "ISBN" nil